Lists¶

In [2]:
products = ["Next-Gen Firewall", "Traps", "Autofocus", "VM-Series", "Cortex"]
In [3]:
products[0]
Out[3]:
'Next-Gen Firewall'
In [4]:
products[1]
Out[4]:
'Traps'
In [5]:
products[-1]
Out[5]:
'Cortex'
In [6]:
products[1:4]
Out[6]:
['Traps', 'Autofocus', 'VM-Series']
In [7]:
products.sort()
for product in products:
    print(product)

Autofocus
Cortex
Next-Gen Firewall
Traps
VM-Series
In [8]:
for index, product in enumerate(products, 1):
    print(f"{index}. {product}")

1. Autofocus
2. Cortex
3. Next-Gen Firewall
4. Traps
5. VM-Series
